    "More robustness and extension analyses are presented in online Appendix B.",
    "In this subsection we consider further robustness and extensions of our approach.",
    "These include using dynamic panel methods robust to endogeneity, controlling for temperature levels, and alternative identification of shocks.",
    "To account for endogeneity and whether our evidence is contingent upon specific empirical methods we can generalise our results by using Generalised Methods of Moments (GMM) estimation from Blundell and Bond (1998), Blundell et al. (2001), Blundell and Bond (2000) and Windmeijer (2005).",
    "Also whilst Bai and Ng (2006, 2008b) and Bai and Ng (2008a) show in linear models that the factor estimates can be treated as known if √ T∕N → 0, as in our case, there may be a question whether generated regressors drive our results."
  ],
